         <abstract>
            <p>In this note it is shown how an integer $x$ can be represented uniquely in a noninteger basis provided the "digits" of the representation are allowed to be nonintegers. It is then shown that the integer parts of these "digits" contain all the information necessary to recover $x$.</p>
